{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "28aadb57-599b-4554-a7e1-aa5a21cd7dd4", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "6f8889f7db9350cc3b3289122ef95d281274b2314ad0ecb90fee68ec81f364c3"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "papptituszpeter", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-01-15", "title": null, "content": "Casting is good, acting is good, however the main plot is kind of predictable. The directing isn't particularly good, the movie doesn't really follow the whole \"show don't tell\" idea. There isn't much to think about, there is no dilemma or something open to interpretation, the good guy is the good guy the bad guy is the bad guy type of movie. It is an easy watch for a weekday evening."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "b45d0a44-fcd9-49eb-9cc3-3fce610523d8", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "ccb83d689b19d7ef4e851977c867d06e18dc0bdf9dbd426bc39bd58131915977"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "eddie_baggins", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-01-15", "title": null, "content": "Despite being a direct adaptation of author Freida McFadden's best-selling book of the same name, a book which has already spawned 2 direct follow-ons, not even the most optimistic of pundits could've predicted just how big The Housemaid has hit over the recent Xmas/New Year period.\n\nClosing in on a global total of $200 plus million at the time of writing, with strong holds everything and much gas still left in the tank, Paul Feig's latest box-office hit proves that when it comes to pulpy thrillers audiences are still more than willing.\n\nBuilding off decent if not exactly rave reviews and some savvy marketing, Housemaid has succeeded where many other like-minded recent Hollywood offerings have failed and it's not hard to see why, as while Feig and his game cast aren't really covering off on any new ground here, with the film baring more than a few similarities to David Fincher's Gone Girl in particular, Housemaid still provides a lot in the way of core level cinematic entertainment that plays to a certain crowd.\n\nFollowing the exploits of Sydney Sweeney's down on her luck newly minted live-in housemaid Millie Calloway who takes on a role at the house of Nina and Andrew Winchester, played by a scene-stealing Amanda Seyfried and an against type Brandon Sklenar, Housemaid has enough twists and turns and audience gasping moments to make it a cinematic spectacle and by embracing its nature, Feig has managed to turn the pulpy into mass audience entertainment that has already been enough to greenlight a sequel.\n\nHousemaid also provides its main star Sweeney her greatest test yet as she morphs into full-time leading lady duties and after the colossal misfires that were Eden and her awards baiting role in the all-time box office stinker Christy, Housemaid allows the global phenomenon to sink her teeth into a layered role that appeases casual audiences.\n\nSweeney's performance here certainly isn't anything overly special, often waiting in Seyfried's shadow but there's enough here to suggest that Sweeney's desire to be more than a socialite and fashionista is a desire that can be backed and met by solid products and performances as long as she continues to surround herself by the right people in the right projects.\n\nArriving at the right place and right time, there's a fair portion of misses that are thrown by Feig's film but an ample amount of hits, marking Housemaid down as a fun and topical thriller that if nothing less sends a fair share portion of its audience off to the hairdressers to take care of their roots asap.\n\nFinal Say -\n\nEmbracing it's over the top premise and overcoming its stumbles with a solid core cast and frequent twists and turns, The Housemaid offers a fresh spin on a familiar set-up on its way to becoming one of recent memories most surprising smash-hits.\n\n3 strands of hair out of 5."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "f9b1837b-6065-4082-9ab8-3022dd9810b1", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "2139b7935a88401dd9b5a00c11ab43ab383ed56119089c33092a6964e5b47c15"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "jimndebj", "rating": 10, "date": "2025-12-19", "title": null, "content": "This movie was just awesome (unhinged, in the best way possible!) A lot of suspense, camp, and dark humor. Small little differences from the book but didn't change the main story at all! I recommend reading the book first; I think you'll enjoy the movie more if you do. The casting was superb; awesome adaptation of the book. Highly recommend!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "351d0ef8-ad0f-425e-b636-0dbffd4f2067", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "aab93bf50caa4b8befa0d91361f404d23bcc93f197e1534ff3142bc03b19d6d8"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "annalucy89", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-01-21", "title": null, "content": "I just came from the theater seeing this movie and wanted to write a little review. Firstly, I had no idea the movie came from a book, not until I read a couple of reviews here so I wasn't comparing it to anything and was able to enjoy it as is. Honestly, If you're not able to judge a media on its own merits then you definitely shouldn't be reading the book beforehand. But anyway, I enjoyed the movie, it wasn't anything groundbreaking and I had kinda figured out the plot a little more than halfway through or so, but it was still enjoyable enough. Amanda Siegfried was definitely the standout with her fantastic performance, Brandon Sklenar was also great, but Sidney Sweeney however was an absolutely drag! I've never seen her in anything else before so I don't know if this is how the director told her to be or if she's just not a great actress, but her acting was actually quite distracting from the main plot. It was just so dry, dull, blank and uninspired that I actually got annoyed a couple times throughout, because she was as stiff as a board and as enjoyable as paint drying. She's got a killer body though, damn! I'm a woman btw, so this isn't coming from some h**ny frat boy! ;) I just wanted to mention it since they made such a showing off of it, as they should, it's gorgeous, but man is her acting super boring. I did feel that the movie dragged a bit, rarely do I say that a movie was too long, because if I enjoy a movie I say the longer the better! But this one felt like it was at least 15 min too long, and some scenes felt very forced and kinda ridiculous, for example the final scene of the movie. I didn't need all that bit with Millie enjoying putting Andrew through some revenge game, not that the dude didn't deserve it, it just felt pointless to the overall plot. I also definitely didn't need the Avengers level final scene where Millie is now apparently the husband killer? I don't even know what that was supposed to mean, but it was unnecessary. Overall it was a fun movie, that Amanda and Brandon, who's effin' gorgeous btw, definitely saved with their great performances! Maybe Sidney will get better in the future as she gets more roles, who knows. The movie is quite predictable and definitely wants to have a feminist theme about domestic violence, which I didn't mind since it's absolutely a very real thing and I found it to be a very good message that DV is happening behind doors you'd least expect it, but if you can look past all the flaws the movie has then you're gonna have a quite a bit of fun with this little thriller."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "6b494686-c2dc-4328-8432-76729118f83b", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "c39bb6431cfeeff28c4b0bd5dcb0d160c3e7e39d70e2cf363c670e4b12141752"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "UrbonasG", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-01-23", "title": null, "content": "Despite this being a 2025 movie, Lithuania just premiered this movie yesterday. Had the chance to see it tonight and I'm so glad I did. I absolutely loved the movie. It probably helps because I have not read the books prior to watching this (certainly motivated me to actually pick up the books) but I genuinely found the movie to be an amazing thriller with a very unexpected twist at the end. I loved both of these actresses as well, I thought both of them acted very well, Nina (Amanda) absolutely shined in her role and Millie (Sydney) was amazing.\n\nPatiently waiting for The Housemaid 2, if it happens. Until then, I guess I'll enjoy the 3 books."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "1b6757ca-5947-4633-aaa3-99cd9927bea8", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "43810ea21f098ac9f61ebb7534aee133b8bd45ad09b4b5af89786094bd98cb7b"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "Jalexs13", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-01-12", "title": null, "content": "The Housemaid maintains interest thanks to a steady pace and well-executed twists that make its more than two-hour runtime feel engaging rather than heavy. Sydney gradually delivers performances that align with her growing international profile, while Amanda steals the film with an intense and fully convincing performance, possibly the best of her career. Each of her scenes successfully conveys the complexity of the character. The ending leaves you wanting more, in a good way.\n\nHowever, Brandon's character fails to establish himself as a truly intimidating presence, and Elizabeth Perkins' role, while interesting and seemingly important, does not add much relevance and mainly serves to reinforce the development of the \"villain.\"\n\nDespite these details, it remains an entertaining, well-acted, and effective thriller. Bonus points for the Taylor Swift song during the end credits."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "a3225c56-5fff-4a90-8275-1a70e8850fe5", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "964adc7fc491b3112f254b9899140378404c24a579fce3212425d0e5cf395172"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "kent-43032", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-01-20", "title": null, "content": "Nice twist towards the end. The husband seemed too good to be true, and towards the end, you find out why. The housemaid character was well played; however, how the movie addressed her alignment with the husband seemed to happen too quickly. Maybe in the book, it's drawn out more, and the buildup to the alignment was able to be more developed. The husband played the main character in the Paramount series \"1923.\""}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "077c924e-992c-4d7b-b06f-984e8bdc5142", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "234aea91383deb9e7ec25cdfd2044734a471fb44b2e99c69a4850910fbcd9c2c"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "bmann-67049", "rating": 7, "date": "2025-12-20", "title": null, "content": "Wasn't sure but decided to check it out. You knew that something was amiss but it wasn't revealed until much later thanks to a couple of twists. Seen better but there's enough with the random funny moments to keep you in it to the end. When you get there, they finish with a nice touch.....have to wait and see!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "b75f0c8a-601c-4aed-a3fb-fbb9e74ed109", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "04224a753e452c120702b0156fbbb5495ae69b10ab4705ce587c2d1689ed3dda"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "bironsesq", "rating": 1, "date": "2025-12-27", "title": null, "content": "What a ridiculous movie this was. The plot is full of holes, nothing is believable and it's almost 2 1/2 hours long to make things even worse. It's such a shame that Hollywood continues to put out trash like this. I will give props to Seyfried, she's a good actress and deserves something way better than this trash. Sydney Sweeney looks mostly homeless during the movie. The popcorn in the candy was way better don't waste your time unless you're used to low expectations."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "1a75250e-72e0-4ee5-b98f-746f2700c3a1", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "eaa0c52b2d2ac0bfc169beec784b6df263dfa85c82dba3d05581ad30808e6b38"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "dekif", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-01-17", "title": null, "content": "8/10 as a parody movie, I was laughing my a** off through most of the film.\n\n4/10 if it was intended to be serious so 6/10?\n\nI guess Amanda Seyfried's performance in the first half of the movie was good and worth mentioning.\n\nJust a heads up, this is not a mystery movie so if you're looking for one, I'd recommend a different option."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "54b77a45-18fb-43d4-bf89-23040bc9cbc8", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "3af5a8e9ce8b9edb52c1dc4ed0b621aa6e4517421611857bf9b4867f881b2e4b"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "steviegjd", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-01-08", "title": null, "content": "This movie combines several movie genres. It also keeps you guessing, which is fun, It seems like it's going one way, the. It shifts and shifts again. There are some extremely amusing moments. It's not art. But it's fun. When you get to the end, if you're not totally uptight, you'll have enjoyed the ride. It's not an oscar movie. But it's fun. Seeing Amanda Seyfried in this and in The Testament of Ann Lee is quite an acting tour de force."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "8f93adec-899b-4bd2-89a0-32ef7d740951", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "3a820eb2efa54d2c831dec0e23a83e9c67044c0d40d29757cb0f995ad5adf2dd"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "Criticalstaff", "rating": 6, "date": "2025-12-31", "title": null, "content": "It is the story of a woman. A young woman who has fallen on hard times. She is sleeping in her car. She lies to get a job. To get a pay check. It sounds too good to be true. It's a housemaid position for a wealthy family. The picture-perfect family. The big house, the nice cars, the actual picture portraits of themselves on the wall.\n\nSlowly, it starts to unravel. The woman of the house who hired her is unreliable. She's beautiful, composed and warm at first but then emerges a coldness, a manic energy. Her husband is warm, tranquil and tender. Like a steady mast in the middle of a storm.\n\nThe young woman begins to dream a bit. She daydreams about the husband. The husband is dreamy, great hair and beautiful teeth. Everybody loves the husband. Everybody except for the wife, who's increasingly erratic and relentless. She starts being cruel, abusive. Like a personified harpy.\n\nWe learn that the young woman is out on parole, that explains why she does any of this, that is why she accepts the abuse. That is why she puts up with the crazy.\n\nThe fate of these three is intertwined. The woman, the wife, the husband. The suburban drama predictably fulfils itself when the husband succumbs to the woman; or the opposite, it's not clear anymore.\n\nThe film then contorts its storytelling. Present becomes past, we see the suffering that the wife and the woman had to endure. The boringly pedestrian love triangle is a haven from difficult and excruciating circumstances. The wife becomes redeemed. By her suffering, by the loss of her agency. She feigned madness only to escape from the grips of the husband.\n\nIn a sea of hardship, guilt, remorse, it turns out the husband is the ultimate evil. The only one who's evil without redeeming reason. The woman and the wife act selfishly or badly, but they have a reason, a logic, however twisted it may be. The husband has no logic for his cruel actions, only perhaps a distant mommy complex. The wife's odd behaviour was only a way to subtract herself from a monster.\n\nThen comes another surprise, the woman was in prison for murder. The face of downtrodden innocence, has actually blood on her hands. The wife out, the husband revealing his true abject nature, she can unleash. She can drop the mask, she can let the fangs out.\n\nIt is the story of a woman, but it was the wife's story all along. Trapped in a marriage, trapped in wealth. Trapped in the picture perfect family. Disappointingly, the film never really understands its own irony. It doesn't argue with the fakeness of it all, with the shallowness. It never quite posits those as cruel or dehumanizing in and of themselves. It doesn't ask anything about the picture-perfect life, it doesn't question it. That would have made this film worthwhile. Instead it twists itself enough to make sense."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "9c4d01a3-e8e1-43bb-b82a-6cda286ae4f8", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "57312baa7f1536623faee060e734ab7387fc57d0c5680d0618330c7f9ec158bc"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "paunore", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-01-22", "title": null, "content": "The film works as a solid and well-crafted drama. The story manages to keep the viewer engaged and delivers several emotionally tense moments. However, I feel that much of its impact and commercial success relies heavily on the female cast.\n\nAmanda Seyfried brings depth and restraint to her role, while Sydney Sweeney, although effective, delivers a performance that feels very similar to her previous work. Once again, she portrays the archetype of a na\u00efve young woman with a strong sexual undertone, making her performance predictable and not particularly daring.\n\nOverall, it's an enjoyable film, but one that likely wouldn't be as successful or widely discussed without the presence and weight of its leading actresses."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "da2a0be7-8467-4c90-a205-4e68ad8f25d9", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "bdea598c165b039372798b1645d4b216c18e6337502bf0f5684ae292c75ad7bf"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "filmtravel101", "rating": 6, "date": "2025-12-31", "title": null, "content": "I did not read the book so I walked into theatre completely unaware of the script being based on a novel.\n\nMain draw was 2 main hot actresses and the cool hunk Sklenar from 1923 that was brilliant in that series and perfect for this role.\n\nThe 1/2nd act were good set ups and nice flow and Sweeney almost reminds one of a younger version of Seyfried so a brilliant casting job.\n\nThe only minor issues were the flashbacks in 2/3rd act that slowed the pacing of the film and also the very limited time of under developed Enzo who seemed out of place and a miscast looking like a Chippendale dancer rather than a gardener.\n\nOtherwise loved the build up and twists and was hoping it would be more lengthy in fun torture of Sklenar but a bit surprised the 3rd act ended so quickly yet it was an extremely entertaining film.\n\nKudos to Seyfried who was phenomenal in her lead role - and I do not understand why some hate Sweeney acting as she is putting out some great roles lately esp in Eden and Christy.\n\n7 stars but could have been a 8/9 if script was better."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "21ba32a9-40f1-45c9-aae3-22ff8c2915b3", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "e720252a041e9d71558388b67762832eca13b78472031cfe88892cdf756c6d6b"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "moijedis", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-01-25", "title": null, "content": "In a luxurious property in the United States, an apparently respectable couple and a cleaning lady who are seeking a winning return from her troubled past will live side by side in pain.\n\nThe film by Paul Feig inspired by Freida McFadden's best seller can be considered a great film. All the intriguing, chilling elements, the manipulation of spirits are transcribed with accuracy and fidelity in the cinematographic work. We face complex, tortured and also proud personalities... The lady of the house, under the influence of a husband who will prove to be diabolical, has developed a strategy that will involve her young employee newly recruited. We will enjoy the performances of Sydney Sweeney and Amanda Seyfried. Attention: we will keep our young children away from disturbing scenes..."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "50917262-f9f5-4393-b457-cf7344a85823", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "9e259bb1309954b861c42ccb0d5a5414a295be009a9f81d86f4d45909d6de4a2"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "emieltijtgat", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-01-07", "title": null, "content": "The movie was okay, but it was very slow. After 80 minutes nothing really important had happened yet, they could shorten the movie by leaving some unimportant scenes behind. Plot twist is also kind of predictable. It is obvious that there has to be something weird about Andrew as they try to make us believe he is perfect. The acting was good."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "391e6cec-9d11-4369-af24-c1a51b59e037", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "25421336c4b8bd0adddf5c57889b5fe4716cc26be584f6a7fbf8218e35f45a4c"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "SimonH-925", "rating": 9, "date": "2025-12-19", "title": null, "content": "I am a big fan of the book, and had very low expectations for this movie, especially that I wasn't very happy with the casting. However, I was pleasantly impressed!!\n\nThey try to stay true to the book, with some changes where it makes sense. All in all, great movie, and I hope they continue with the remainder of the series.\n\nHighly recommend!!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "080834fe-5013-467d-835f-8c5f7f245d21", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "a5884afb31803496c3e38a62db2e3c6a9220dec3626cd9cdb47fa418cc998d78"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "Emma-1368", "rating": null, "date": "2026-01-11", "title": null, "content": "I went into this movie extremely excited only to be let down. I read the book prior to seeing the movie and absolutely loved it! One of my fav books! I was so sad to see that the movie did not live up to the hype. For the most part I was not impressed with Sydney Sweeney's acting thought they could have casted someone a little better to play the role of Millie. I thought Amanda played a great Nina I feel she really fit the vibe. Overall this is the type of movie where the book is just better."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "446353b5-7919-4077-b720-576082713362", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "9cb309a00eb7a217833077c9c42b0ae6a6c30df1d9f7b02505bf87443b4e168e"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "kajushsim", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-01-13", "title": null, "content": "The movie itself is good. Generally good cast, good plot, good plot. BUT... I read the book two days before. If I were to rate the movie based on the book, the movie would get a LOT lower rating. I know you can't make a movie identical to the book, but some important information was completely lost. Information that is actually very important for the entire story. First of all: I absolutely adore Amanda, but in the book Nina has a lot of weight. Not exactly the right choice of actress. Second of all: what's with the ending? Hello?? The third act sucks. I won't even talk about the other plots and information, but it's definitely not the best movie based on the book. The last thing I have to admit: I personally don't think they need to push Sydney Sweeney everywhere, but honestly, she somehow fit the role of Millie.\n\nMy rating is based on the book-based movie. \u2728"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "e0edc509-439f-495a-b990-63bf66073ab7", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "963c9e45c787151a0bd0fd2b0719ceab05f54be30c9d74d5eb2f8fd709fd904a"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "tdnhkwss", "rating": 1, "date": "2025-12-27", "title": null, "content": "I walked out of the screening before it even ended because of how utterly stupid the film is. Every character operates on ridiculous, surreal premises. At times it genuinely feels like watching situations straight out of a porn movie: flimsy excuses just to parade the new blonde girl and the so-called husband, who fills every shot with smirking looks, idiotic facial expressions meant to be charming, and muscle-flexing poses. The fact that people can actually enjoy trash like this says a lot about the deeply troubling state of the social and cultural fabric of the world we live in."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "26795e35-456a-47f2-aa2f-c7d4cb9eaa0a", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "0d9e098c2ee0ae3834078af8fd5b887cc22c03a66a79c5f1502af9d7193cd56b"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "alibabs123", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-01-08", "title": null, "content": "A pretty solid thriller but it's more 'Sleeping with the Enemy' than 'Cape Fear'.\n\nI think the casting choices were interesting however Miss Seyfried's performance was more than enough to paper over the cracks of her female counterparts', slightly less charismatic offering. But let's face it, Miss Sweeney was not hired for her Golden Globe-littered r\u00e9sum\u00e9 but rather to 'litter' portions of the movie with her golden...ahem... globes.\n\nThat being said, I think Mr. Feig was almost onto something here and was close to producing a real serious thriller for the times. This is a book adaptation but I can't comment on which was better or why as I have not read and do not intend to read said book. I just think, whether intended or not, there were a few too many comedic moments in places where they weren't needed. No spoilers but towards the end during a few moments that could have really bolstered the creation of a terrifying character and if had been handled only slightly differently, could have maybe become iconic, a cheap laugh was favoured over something darker and with this, the aura of the villain gets diluted. Perhaps this was to stay true to the book, for fear of backlash from hoards of the half-moon-glasses wearing brigade, who will only accept verbatim adaptations of their treasured literary masterpieces. Or Mr. Feig wanted to stay true to himself. Refusing to cut the comedic apron strings, the very thing that brought him to the dance."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "9d4ec5bf-c093-4f54-8887-b03d1ed6ff91", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "8b30cdcb1670eb74515cddf46b5650ffc39127437a75c82c206534e66bb94cbe"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "Always_green86", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-01-01", "title": null, "content": "I didn't knw what to expect before watching which is probably why I enjoyed it..I did think I would end up turning it off based on predictably but it was the opposite and definitely draws you in the more you watch .with a a plot twist tht surly wasn't easy to predict at first. Overall good story.........."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "19c93864-750b-4a81-919e-07c3b4b15228", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "f15ae240613e86dcb3d636c23e49c57f7c7840c7266666d06737a1c9a13b5a86"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "leonmladosic", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-01-06", "title": null, "content": "As I said in the title, finally a good refreshment in the cinema, a thriller that \"everybody\" will watch. Sydney really sold the movie, if it wasn't for her it would probably be a box office bomb.\n\nThe movie starts somewhat good, then the lets call them flashback scenes take way too much time of the movie so we knew the twist before it actually happened so there's that. The story is good, but the entire thing could have been executed better, the acting is remarkable. Did not read the book so I am not comparing the movie to it."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "86b0b577-db40-4a05-8095-fecad2ae3ad1", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:23.254173", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "7f27df8c55df7a044c7016a0fe1dab7ccf9ec700ba645490084daa3a0c7e403c"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt27543632", "author": "turnerfan77", "rating": 8, "date": "2025-12-23", "title": null, "content": "I was excited to see this movie because I loved Freida McFadden's book and I wanted to see how well it translated to the big screen. I hoped for the best but was prepared for it to be terrible. Thankfully the Paul Feig delivered a good adaptation of the book. This had a great cast. Amanda Seyfried was amazing! I haven't enjoyed her acting in a very long time but she brought Nina Winchester to life perfectly! Brandon Sklenar was fantastic too! There are rumors of him being the new Batman and during the first half of this movie it felt like he was channeling Bruce Wayne and now I hope the rumors are true! Sydney Sweeney does a decent job as Millie Calloway but she really shines in the back half of the movie. They did such a good job of making you think this is one thing and then switch it up and once they do that the movie takes off! While this is a good movie there are a couple things that bothered me...the length of the movie. It felt very long during the first half and if you read the book you were just waiting for that moment when things really start to take off so that first half dragged just a bit. The second thing is really a nitpick but at times Sweeney's line delivery was awful. She is good in this but there were just a couple of those moments that made me think how did she pull of her great performance in Christy. This is definitely a must see! A great thriller that is great anti programming to the new Avatar. Don't wait for this to hit streaming see this in theaters!\n\nBy The Numbers breakdown: Cast-8 Acting-8 Trailer-10 Ending-9 Story-9 Visuals-7 Direction-8 Sound-8 Genre-9 Sub Genre-9 The Faces For Radio score - 85."}}
